President Obama has announced his intent to appoint several individuals to key administration posts. These include Janine Davidson, Lieutenant General Dennis M. McCarthy, F. Whitten Peters, Margaret C. Harrell, Hyman Bass, Carlos Castillo-Chavez, and Joseph S. Francisco. Davidson is an assistant professor at George Mason University and a senior fellow at the Center for a New American Security. McCarthy is a principal for The Military Experts, a consulting firm, and previously served as Assistant Secretary of Defense for Reserve Affairs. Peters is a partner at Williams & Connolly LLP and served as Secretary of the Air Force from 1999 to 2001. Harrell is the Director of the Army Health Program at the RAND Corporation. Bass is a distinguished university professor of mathematics and mathematics education at the University of Michigan. Castillo-Chavez is a professor at Arizona State University and has been involved in various mathematical and scientific institutes. Francisco is a professor at Purdue University and focuses on spectroscopy, kinetics, and photochemistry.